<p>The Guggenheim Foundation, which is celebrating its centennial this year, has announced its 2025 Fellows, and a few philosophers are among them.<span id="more-53485"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-38017 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/guggenheim-foundation-logo3-1024x548.jpg" alt="" width="750" height="401" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/guggenheim-foundation-logo3-1024x548.jpg 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/guggenheim-foundation-logo3-300x160.jpg 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/guggenheim-foundation-logo3-768x411.jpg 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/guggenheim-foundation-logo3-400x214.jpg 400w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/guggenheim-foundation-logo3.jpg 1182w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" /></p>
<p>They are:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://philosophy.berkeley.edu/ginsborg" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Hannah Ginsborg</strong></a>, Willis S. and Marion Slusser Professor of Philosophy at the University of California, Berkeley</li>
<li><strong><a href="https://faculty.sites.uci.edu/shuttegg/" rel="home">Simon Huttegger</a></strong>, Chancellor’s Professor of Logic and Philosophy of Science at the University of California, Irvine</li>
<li><strong><a href="https://law2.wm.edu/faculty/bios/fulltime/jgdwye.php" target="_blank" rel="noopener">James Dwyer</a></strong>, Cabell Research Professor and Professor of Law at the College of William and Mary.</li>
</ul>
<p>The fellowships are for 6-12 months, with monetary awards of varying amounts, and are given with no strings attached. The full list of new fellows is <a href="https://www.gf.org/stories/announcing-the-2025-guggenheim-fellows#2025-fellows" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/04/15/philosophers-among-new-guggenheim-fellows-2/">Philosophers Among New Guggenheim Fellows</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>